The for..in and for..of loops, gives us a clean and concise syntax to iterate on iterable items like arrays, strings, objects, and enumerables. Now the question is where to use which. Here&rsquo;s a little reminder to get you you started.
for..in Use this to iterate over the properties of an object:
let person = { name: &#39;Francis&#39;, alias: &#39;codehakase&#39;, eyeColour: &#39;brown&#39; }; for(let key in person) { console.log( `${key}=&gt; ${person[key]}` ); } // name =&gt; Francis // alias =&gt; codehakase .
